author: Michael Larabel
description: The open-source Valkey key-value database that is forked from Redis is preparing for the big Valkey 9.0 feature release. Valkey 9.0-rc1 was issued today and comes with some exciting performance optimizations and other enhancements for this in-memory KV database...
title: Valkey 9.0-rc1 Taps AVX-512 For String-To-Integer Conversion For ~19% Gain

author: Michael Larabel
description: Oracle today released VirtualBox 7.2 as the newest version of this cross-platform virtualization solution...
title: VirtualBox 7.2 Released With Windows 11 ARM Support, Linux 6.16 Compatibility

author: Michael Larabel
description: The newly-launched AMD Ryzen Threadripper 9000 series headlined by the 64-core Threadripper 9980X and 32-core Threadripper 9970X offer incredible performance and a wonderful addition to the Zen 5 family for the HEDT space. But there is also the Threadripper PRO 9000 series with the flagship Threadripper PRO 9995WX sporting 96 cores. In this article is a look at how that 96-core AMD Threadripper PRO 9995WX performs using a TRX50 platform with quad channel DDR5-6400 memory.
title: AMD Ryzen Threadripper PRO 9995WX Performance With TRX50 + Quad Channel DDR5

author: Michael Larabel
description: KDE Gear 25.08 is out this morning as the newest feature release to this collection of KDE applications...
title: KDE Gear 25.08 Released With Improvements For Many KDE Apps

author: Michael Larabel
description: Sent out today was the first DRM-Misc-Next pull request to DRM-Next for queuing ahead of the Linux 6.18 merge window opening around early October. There are a number of smaller DRM graphics driver improvements ready as well as continued work around the accelerator "accel" drivers for the increasing number of NPUs in devices...
title: AMDXDNA Improvements & New Rockchip NPU Accelerator Driver For Linux 6.18

author: Michael Larabel
description: Next year's LibreOffice 26.2 open-source office suite is set to better handle documents with restricted embedded fonts. This is for dealing with situations where fonts may have restricted licensing rights and where up to now LibreOffice Writer simply hasn't dealt with them correctly...
title: LibreOffice 26.2 To Better Handle Documents With Restricted Embedded Fonts
